:rice_ball: [@union-find/non-contiguous](https://union-find.github.io/non-contiguous) ==


User:Svjo / CC BY-SA 3.0

Non-contiguously-allocated disjoint-set data structures for JavaScript. See [docs](https://union-find.github.io/non-contiguous/index.html). Parent is [js-data-structures](https://github.com/make-github-pseudonymous-again/js-data-structures). ```js find( a ) === find( b ) ; // false union( A , B ) ; find( a ) === find( b ) ; // true ``` content:
# Installation

Can be managed using
[yarn](https://yarnpkg.com/en/docs),
[npm](https://docs.npmjs.com),
or [jspm](https://jspm.org/docs).


### yarn
```terminal
yarn add @union-find/non-contiguous
```

### npm
```terminal
npm install @union-find/non-contiguous --save
```

### jspm
```terminal
jspm install npm:@union-find/non-contiguous
```
